  "text": "The HotSpot JIT compilation pipeline is orchestrated by CompileBroker (compileBroker.hpp), which manages all compilation requests. It maintains two CompileQueues (_c1_compile_queue and _c2_compile_queue) and an array of AbstractCompiler pointers (_compilers[2]). CompilerThread (compilerThread.hpp) extends JavaThread and is the thread type that executes compilations; each holds a reference to an AbstractCompiler. AbstractCompiler (abstractCompiler.hpp) is the base class declaring the compile_method() virtual function. C1 (c1_Compiler.hpp, class Compiler) and C2 (c2compiler.hpp, class C2Compiler) both extend AbstractCompiler and implement the two tiers of JIT compilation. The compilation policy selects tier levels 0-4 (interpreter through C2) based on profiling data and queue lengths.",
